'''Gregory Dale Bear''' ([[August 20]], [[1950s|1951]]–[[November 19]], [[2022]])<ref name="Death" /> was an American science fiction and mainstream author of the novel ''[[Rogue Planet]]''. His work has covered themes of galactic conflict ([[Wikipedia:The Forge of God|''Forge of God'']] books), artificial universes ([[Wikipedia:Eon (novel)|''Eon'']] series), consciousness and cultural practices, and accelerated evolution ([[Wikipedia:Blood Music|''Blood Music'']], [[Wikipedia:Darwin's Radio|''Darwin's Radio'']], and ''[[Wikipedia:Darwin's Children|Darwin's Children]]'').

